%h1 Chains
%hr
%strong Chains connect social media triggers with specific actuators performed by reporter.box. e.g: A tweet with hashtag "#light_on" will switcg a light bulb connected to a reporter box on. These are all your chains:
%hr
%h3 Manage Chains
%strong Create a new chain to make your sensor-live-report more interactive!
%p
=link_to new_chain_path, {:class => "btn btn-primary btn-lg"} do
  %span.glyphicon.glyphicon-plus-sign
  Create new chain

%hr
%h3 Listing chains
%strong This is a list of all your chains. Click on them with actuator, function and hashtag.

%table.table.table-striped.table-hover
  %thead
    %tr
      %th Hashtag
      %th Actuator
      %th Function
      %th Controls
      %th
      %th

  %tbody
    - @chains.each do |chain|
      %tr
        %td= chain.hashtag
        %td= chain.actuator
        %td= chain.function        
        %td= link_to 'Show', chain
        %td= link_to 'Edit', edit_chain_path(chain)
        %td= link_to 'Destroy', chain, :method => :delete, :data => { :confirm => 'Are you sure?' }

%br

